body:
I want to create helper methods that wrap some functionalities like this one for example

```chsharp
public bool IsImage(Stream stream) => SKCodec.Create(stream) != null;
```

The problem is that it created SKCodec and it is disposable, so we have to dispose it, but if we do like this

```csharp
public bool IsImage(Stream stream) 
{
    using(var codec = SKCodec.Create(stream))
    {
        return codec != null;
    }
}
```
It will also dispose the stream, and I obviously don't want to dispose the stream.

So I ended up returning Disposable wrapper or the SKCodec itself, so the client can dispose it when done with the stream. which makes my helper methods very useless wrappers that encapsulate nothing.

I think an object shouldn't dispose a resource that it doesn't own, if the Stream is passed to SKCodec, SKCodec should not dispose it because the client could be still using it.
